msgid "Stepper motor acceleration limits"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"With delta kinematics it is possible for a move that is accelerating "
"in cartesian space to require an acceleration on a particular stepper"
" motor greater than the move's acceleration. This can occur when a "
"stepper arm is more horizontal than vertical and the line of movement"
" passes near that stepper's tower. Although these moves could require"
" a stepper motor acceleration greater than the printer's maximum "
"configured move acceleration, the effective mass moved by that "
"stepper would be smaller. Thus the higher stepper acceleration does "
"not result in significantly higher stepper torque and it is therefore"
" considered harmless."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"However, to avoid extreme cases, Klipper enforces a maximum ceiling "
"on stepper acceleration of three times the printer's configured "
"maximum move acceleration. (Similarly, the maximum velocity of the "
"stepper is limited to three times the maximum move velocity.) In "
"order to enforce this limit, moves at the extreme edge of the build "
"envelope (where a stepper arm may be nearly horizontal) will have a "
"lower maximum acceleration and velocity."
msgstr ""

